To automate selecting all checkboxes on a page and then save them when you click a "Save" button, you can use JavaScript or jQuery. Here’s a simple example using vanilla JavaScript:

1. Select all checkboxes.
2. Check each checkbox.
3. Add an event listener to the "Save" button to trigger the selection.

### Vanilla JavaScript Example

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Checkbox Automation</title>
</head>
<body>

<input type="checkbox" name="chk"> Checkbox 1<br>
<input type="checkbox" name="chk"> Checkbox 2<br>
<input type="checkbox" name="chk"> Checkbox 3<br>
<button id="saveButton">Save</button>

<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    // Select all checkboxes
    const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

    // Function to check all checkboxes
    function selectAllCheckboxes() {
        checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => checkbox.checked = true);
    }

    // Get the save button
    const saveButton = document.getElementById('saveButton');

    // Add event listener to the save button
    saveButton.addEventListener('click', selectAllCheckboxes);
});
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### jQuery Example

If you prefer to use jQuery, here's how you can do it:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Checkbox Automation</title>
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>

<input type="checkbox" name="chk"> Checkbox 1<br>
<input type="checkbox" name="chk"> Checkbox 2<br>
<input type="checkbox" name="chk"> Checkbox 3<br>
<button id="saveButton">Save</button>

<script>
$(document).ready(function() {
    // Select all checkboxes
    const checkboxes = $('input[type="checkbox"]');

    // Function to check all checkboxes
    function selectAllCheckboxes() {
        checkboxes.prop('checked', true);
    }

    // Get the save button
    const saveButton = $('#saveButton');

    // Add event listener to the save button
    saveButton.click(selectAllCheckboxes);
});
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

Both examples achieve the same goal: when the "Save" button is clicked, all checkboxes are checked.

